</summary><category term="kindness"></category><category term="charity"></category><category term="fun"></category><category term="community"></category></entry><entry><title>31 Days of Kindness (Day 5) - 2015 Edition</title><link href="http://larry.wapnitsky.com/posts/2015/Aug/05/31-days-of-kindness-day-5-2015-edition.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-08-04T00:00:00-04:00</updated><author><name>Larry G. Wapnitsky</name></author><id>tag:larry.wapnitsky.com,2015-08-05:posts/2015/Aug/05/31-days-of-kindness-day-5-2015-edition.html</id><summary type="html">

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="Block_image" src="/images/news/31DaysOfKindness2015/31-Days-of-Kindness.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Welcome to Day 5 of &lt;a href="/posts/2015/Jul/30/31-days-of-kindness-2015-edition.html" target="_blank"&gt;#31DaysOfKindness&lt;/a&gt;, 2015&amp;nbsp;edition!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Give a hug to someone who deserves it. Easier said than done, right? My family gets hugs all the time, and they are well deserved. Now was the day to step outside of that circle to share. Who did I hug? Well, it wasn&amp;rsquo;t physical (more of a virtual check-in by phone-call), but it was a recently-made friend who&amp;rsquo;s been going through some rather rough&amp;nbsp;stuff.&lt;/p&gt;
</summary><category term="kindness"></category><category term="charity"></category><category term="fun"></category><category term="community"></category></entry><entry><title>31 Days of Kindness (Day 4) - 2015 Edition</title><link href="http://larry.wapnitsky.com/posts/2015/Aug/04/31-days-of-kindness-day-4-2015-edition.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-08-04T00:00:00-04:00</updated><author><name>Larry G. Wapnitsky</name></author><id>tag:larry.wapnitsky.com,2015-08-04:posts/2015/Aug/04/31-days-of-kindness-day-4-2015-edition.html</id><summary type="html">

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="Block_image" src="/images/news/31DaysOfKindness2015/31-Days-of-Kindness.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Welcome to Day 4 of &lt;a href="/posts/2015/Jul/30/31-days-of-kindness-2015-edition.html" target="_blank"&gt;#31DaysOfKindness&lt;/a&gt;, 2015&amp;nbsp;edition!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While the theme for today is to share an article with someone, I&amp;rsquo;m going to take inspiration from &lt;a href="http://RyanAvery.com" target="_blank"&gt;Ryan Avery&lt;/a&gt; and share &lt;span class="caps"&gt;ALL&lt;/span&gt; the articles from one of my favorite blogs with you - &lt;a href="http://www.runnersworld.com/tag/the-big-guy-blog" target="_blank"&gt;The Big Guy Blog&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href="http://runnersworld.com" target="_blank"&gt;Runner&amp;rsquo;s World&lt;/a&gt; as written by &lt;a href="http://tedspiker.com" target="_blank"&gt;Ted Spiker&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why the entire blog and all of its articles? Read on and find&amp;nbsp;out&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;
</summary><category term="kindness"></category><category term="charity"></category><category term="fun"></category><category term="community"></category></entry><entry><title>31 Days of Kindness (Day 3) - 2015 Edition</title><link href="http://larry.wapnitsky.com/posts/2015/Aug/03/31-days-of-kindness-day-3-2015-edition.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-08-03T00:00:00-04:00</updated><author><name>Larry G. Wapnitsky</name></author><id>tag:larry.wapnitsky.com,2015-08-03:posts/2015/Aug/03/31-days-of-kindness-day-3-2015-edition.html</id><summary type="html">

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="Block_image" src="/images/news/31DaysOfKindness2015/31-Days-of-Kindness.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Welcome to Day 3 of &lt;a href="/posts/2015/Jul/30/31-days-of-kindness-2015-edition.html" target="_blank"&gt;#31DaysOfKindness&lt;/a&gt;, 2015&amp;nbsp;edition!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For me, I know I&amp;rsquo;m sometimes a beast without a cup of coffee in morning. I may be a little addicted, but I can go a few days or more without my&amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;fix&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, I got to make someone happy with a little morning boost of caffeine to feed their own little&amp;nbsp;addiction!&lt;/p&gt;
